Follow installation steps here: https://www.sparkcodehub.com/spark/streaming/streaming-start
- kafka
- spark

1. Download apache kafka Binary Download -> https://kafka.apache.org/community/downloads/
-  kafka_2.12-3.7.1.tgz

2. Download spark binary -> https://www.apache.org/dyn/closer.lua/spark/spark-3.5.8/spark-3.5.8-bin-hadoop3.tgz
- spark-3.5.8-bin-hadoop3.tgz

3. for each of the Downloads in 1 and 2, execute the following. For myself, I did (cd ~) first, and then:
- tar -xvzf spark-3.5.8-bin-hadoop3.tgz
- tar -xvzf kafka_2.12-3.7.1.tgz

4. Add these exports to ~/.bashrc:

BASHRC
export SPARK_HOME=$HOME/spark-3.5.8-bin-hadoop3
export PATH=$PATH:$SPARK_HOME/bin

export KAFKA_HOME=$HOME/kafka_2.12-3.7.1
export PATH=$KAFKA_HOME/bin:$PATH 

5. source ~/.bashrc

--> cd ~/kafka_2.12-3.7.1/

6. In Terminal 1: Run: zookeeper-server-start.sh config/zookeeper.properties

7. In Terminal 2: kafka-server-start.sh config/server.properties

8. In Terminal 3: kafka-topics.sh --create --topic sales --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 3 --replication-factor 1 

9. In Terminal 3: spark-submit   --deploy-mode client   --packages org.apache.spark:spark-sql-kafka-0-10_2.12:3.5.0   benchmark_spark.py

10. In Terminal 4: python3 producer.py

11. You can run multiple producers in multiple terminals to send more data to kafka

12. Watch terminal 3 output for 5 second window results. 
Also view data in metrics/ dir. 
